<Layout
	title="About Me"
	description="Au Chun Yin (Jaden)"
	pubDate={new Date('Feb 24 2026')}
	heroImage="/blog-placeholder-about.jpg"
>
	<p>
		Hi, I’m Au Chun Yin (Jaden). I work with live sound and audio production, and I am a student in Music Technology at Oregon State University. 
		Before OSU, I studied Computer Science and finished a Certificate in Audio Engineering at community college. 
		I grew up between Hong Kong and the U.S., and that mix of places is a big part of who I am.
	</p>

	<p>
		I started doing sound in secondary school by helping with assemblies and concerts. 
		I learned how a good mix can change how people feel in a room. Since then, 
		I have worked on student events, small shows, and church services, and I enjoy making things sound clear without stressing people out.
	</p>

	<p>
		Right now I focus on:

		Live sound for small to medium events
		Basic recording and mixing for talks, concerts, and services
		Using tools like Reaper and Pro Tools for editing and clean mixes
	</p>

